column5: It was awesome! Our group had what we feel to be some of the best walleye days ever.

We too had a pretty solid week but not our best on Cedar. For some reason we only found smaller males around Gull island. Outside of one afternoon just outside the east sanctuary, the majority of our fish came from the west side. Our big fish was only 21‚Äù but we boated a fair amount 19-21 inch fish. Most of our eaters and take home fish were 15-16 inches. My group prefers the season opener or the following week so we jumped on an available cabin for the 2024 opener.
